"""Cavern prop sprites: floor debris (b495-496) + room contents (b497).

Pixel-art props stamped onto the drawn cavern by the procedural
renderer (cavern_render.py).

CAVERN_PROPS -- ambient debris scattered on PLAIN floors (bones,
rubble, webs, mushrooms...). Sliced from two checkerboard-keyed debris
sheets, defringed, webs matted translucent, capped 40px.

ROOM_PROPS -- one identity prop per THEMED room type, drawn centered
so the room reads at a glance (altar candelabra, coffins, tomes, iron
grate, cauldron, war banner...). The room letter shrank to a tiny
corner badge (see app.py:_grid_cell_html). Sliced from two
magenta-keyed prop sheets, capped 48px. U/D (ladder/pit) stay
procedural in cavern_render.py; E (entrance) draws nothing.

Debris deliberately excludes anything that reads as LOOT so
decorations never bait a tap; room props deliberately INCLUDE
reward-ish art (gold piles for chest rooms) because those rooms ARE
interactable.
"""

